{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015zvQyPPZKDZQaxPjkSYJ9D","type":"tool_result","content":"## Code Review\n\nThis pull request updates dependencies, but the title 'chore: update patch-level dependencies' and the description's claim of 'Only semver-compatible (patch) updates — no breaking changes' are misleading. The update includes several minor and major version bumps for transitive dependencies, which carry a risk of introducing breaking changes. For example, `dotenv` is updated from v9 to v17, and `es-module-lexer` from v1 to v2. These changes require careful manual review and testing to ensure they don't break the application.\n## Summary of Changes\n\nHello, I'm Gemini Code Assist[^1]! I'm currently reviewing this pull request and will post my feedback shortly. In the meantime, here's a summary to help you and other reviewers quickly get up to speed!\n\nThis pull request performs routine maintenance by updating a wide array of patch-level dependencies across the project. The updates ensure that the codebase remains current with the latest stable versions of its dependencies, addressing potential bug fixes, performance improvements, and minor feature enhancements without introducing breaking changes. This keeps the development environment robust and secure, facilitating smoother future development and reducing technical debt.\n\n### Highlights\n\n* **Dependency Updates**: Updated various patch-level dependencies across the project, including core development tools and libraries.\n* **Remotion Framework**: The Remotion suite of packages (bundler, CLI, compositors, media-utils, player, renderer, studio, streaming, web-renderer, webcodecs) has been updated from version 4.0.407 to 4.0.436.\n* **ESLint and Related Tools**: ESLint and its associated packages, such as `@eslint/config-array`, `@eslint/eslintrc`, and `@eslint/js`, have received patch updates to their latest versions.\n* **Core JavaScript Utilities**: Key utilities like `nanoid` and `prettier` have been updated to their latest patch versions.\n* **TypeScript Type Definitions**: Type definitions for Node.js (`@types/node`) and React (`@types/react`) have been updated to ensure compatibility and leverage the latest typings.\n* **New Dependencies Introduced**: Several new dependencies were introduced, primarily related to `@emnapi`, `@mediabunny`, `@module-federation`, `@napi-rs`, `@rspack`, `@tybys/wasm-util`, `acorn-import-phases`, `error-stack-parser`, `html-entities`, and `stackframe`, indicating expanded functionality or updated internal requirements of other packages.\n* **Dependency Removals**: The `randombytes` and `serialize-javascript` packages were removed, likely due to being replaced by other dependencies or no longer being required.\n\n🧠 **New Feature in Public Preview:** You can now enable **Memory** to help **Gemini Code Assist** learn from your team's feedback. This makes future code reviews more consistent and personalized to your project's style. **Click [here](https://codeassist.google/code-review/login) to enable Memory in your admin console.**\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Changelog</b></summary>\n\n* **package-lock.json**\n    * Updated `@emnapi/core` to 1.9.0\n    * Updated `@emnapi/runtime` to 1.9.0\n    * Updated `@emnapi/wasi-threads` to 1.2.0\n    * Updated `@eslint/config-array` from 0.21.1 to 0.21.2\n    * Updated `@eslint/eslintrc` from 3.3.3 to 3.3.5\n    * Updated `@eslint/js` from 9.39.2 to 9.39.4\n    * Updated `@mediabunny/aac-encoder` to 1.37.0\n    * Updated `@mediabunny/flac-encoder` to 1.37.0\n    * Updated `@mediabunny/mp3-encoder` to 1.37.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/error-codes` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/runtime` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/runtime-core` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/runtime-tools` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/sdk` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/webpack-bundler-runtime` to 0.22.0","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98205e1a-a018-40f3-839d-6f95fb6c6bb7","uuid":"c66a33b8-84da-440f-87de-af32af5681be","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"## Code Review\n\nThis pull request updates dependencies, but the title 'chore: update patch-level dependencies' and the description's claim of 'Only semver-compatible (patch) updates — no breaking changes' are misleading. The update includes several minor and major version bumps for transitive dependencies, which carry a risk of introducing breaking changes. For example, `dotenv` is updated from v9 to v17, and `es-module-lexer` from v1 to v2. These changes require careful manual review and testing to ensure they don't break the application.\n## Summary of Changes\n\nHello, I'm Gemini Code Assist[^1]! I'm currently reviewing this pull request and will post my feedback shortly. In the meantime, here's a summary to help you and other reviewers quickly get up to speed!\n\nThis pull request performs routine maintenance by updating a wide array of patch-level dependencies across the project. The updates ensure that the codebase remains current with the latest stable versions of its dependencies, addressing potential bug fixes, performance improvements, and minor feature enhancements without introducing breaking changes. This keeps the development environment robust and secure, facilitating smoother future development and reducing technical debt.\n\n### Highlights\n\n* **Dependency Updates**: Updated various patch-level dependencies across the project, including core development tools and libraries.\n* **Remotion Framework**: The Remotion suite of packages (bundler, CLI, compositors, media-utils, player, renderer, studio, streaming, web-renderer, webcodecs) has been updated from version 4.0.407 to 4.0.436.\n* **ESLint and Related Tools**: ESLint and its associated packages, such as `@eslint/config-array`, `@eslint/eslintrc`, and `@eslint/js`, have received patch updates to their latest versions.\n* **Core JavaScript Utilities**: Key utilities like `nanoid` and `prettier` have been updated to their latest patch versions.\n* **TypeScript Type Definitions**: Type definitions for Node.js (`@types/node`) and React (`@types/react`) have been updated to ensure compatibility and leverage the latest typings.\n* **New Dependencies Introduced**: Several new dependencies were introduced, primarily related to `@emnapi`, `@mediabunny`, `@module-federation`, `@napi-rs`, `@rspack`, `@tybys/wasm-util`, `acorn-import-phases`, `error-stack-parser`, `html-entities`, and `stackframe`, indicating expanded functionality or updated internal requirements of other packages.\n* **Dependency Removals**: The `randombytes` and `serialize-javascript` packages were removed, likely due to being replaced by other dependencies or no longer being required.\n\n🧠 **New Feature in Public Preview:** You can now enable **Memory** to help **Gemini Code Assist** learn from your team's feedback. This makes future code reviews more consistent and personalized to your project's style. **Click [here](https://codeassist.google/code-review/login) to enable Memory in your admin console.**\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Changelog</b></summary>\n\n* **package-lock.json**\n    * Updated `@emnapi/core` to 1.9.0\n    * Updated `@emnapi/runtime` to 1.9.0\n    * Updated `@emnapi/wasi-threads` to 1.2.0\n    * Updated `@eslint/config-array` from 0.21.1 to 0.21.2\n    * Updated `@eslint/eslintrc` from 3.3.3 to 3.3.5\n    * Updated `@eslint/js` from 9.39.2 to 9.39.4\n    * Updated `@mediabunny/aac-encoder` to 1.37.0\n    * Updated `@mediabunny/flac-encoder` to 1.37.0\n    * Updated `@mediabunny/mp3-encoder` to 1.37.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/error-codes` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/runtime` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/runtime-core` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/runtime-tools` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/sdk` to 0.22.0\n    * Updated `@module-federation/webpac